(1)  Did you setup Cloudera VM on your machine? You just need to write yes or no.
-> Yes

(2) What is the meaning of $HOME in your VM environment?
-> $HOME is an environment variable that contains the location of current user's home directory of the VM environment

(3) What is the meaning of SUDO in Unix/Linux environment?
-> sudo allows a permitted user to execute a command as the superuser or another user.
(4) Write and briefly explain any 5 Unix/Linux commands. 
-> 
cd: change directory
cp: copy contents of one file to another.
mv: move a file to another folder or directory
mkdir: make a new directory
dir: list the contents of a directory
ls: shows the list of files in the current directory.